<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-07-23T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-07-23T12:00:00-05:00" n="277" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.632/8: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Austria</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Washburn</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Vienna</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-07-23T18:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 23,
                                        1923—6 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received July 24—9:11
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>30. Department’s telegram 13, July 19, 5 p.m. Foreign Office is prepared
                            immediately to negotiate general treaty of amity, commerce and consular
                            rights and asks me expressly to say that the Austrian Government is much
                            gratified by the Department’s willingness to conclude such a treaty at
                            this time.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Washburn</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>